                <note rend="inline" type="source">102.1/2–1947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-19T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 19, 1947—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>203. For Adler from Treasury. Cable whether announced changes in monetary policy
                    affect use of Hong Kong open market rate for Navy procurement of yuan. Also
                    request info on any official measures taken to terminate use of US currency for
                    troop pay. [Treasury.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
